x4freetext: The oxygen target, thick self-supporting Be-O films,
approx. 20 mug/cm**2. The oxygen content of the target
was determined in two independent measurements-by
Rutherford backscattering of 2-MeV He-4 ion and by a
comparison between the large angle yield in the
equal E-C.M. Reactions C-12(E=60 MeV)+O-16 and
O-16(E=80 MeV)+C-12 elastic scattering off a C-12
target of known thickness.
Optical model analysis.
Q3D spectrometer.
A position-sensitive proportional counter.
Two position-sensitive silicon detectors, area=
5*1 cm**2, placed 7.8 cm from the target.

accelerator.
The uncertainties were set to be fixed 10% of the
experimental cross section, for all measurements.  In
this way, the angles close to 90-degree, where the
experimental uncertainty can be relatively large due to
the small cross section, have a sufficient weight to
influence the fit.
